beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob:
Great beer. I love tripels and this one spoke to me. It told me that pallet and complexity isn't anything without taste. And this beer had taste. Try it and see. You will become a believer. 

---Crozier
beer_name: Samuel Adams (Barrel Room Collection) New World Tripel

review_blob:
White foamy head. Golden color. Fruity ancient recipe style. Strong bite for a tripel. Not very complex but very well brewed which is a nice retreat in a world of "want to be" complex craft brews. Great smack back to the realm of time when craft brew was just brew. 

---Crozier

One of my favorites. Taste is smooth. Great spices. Absolutely an amazing beer 

---Crozier

Picked up the four pack as a trial but not expecting much. Had no idea that Sierra Nevada had stepped up the hop game and slam dunked this brew. Absolutely amazed coming from the brewery and price. I'm buying more. 

---Crozier

Omg. I love this beer. I have been waiting and trying to get this beer for 1 1/2 years. All the hype and wondering how its going to taste... It didn't let me down. Hints of fruit. Strong taste of alcohol and spices. Well worth the wait and I can't wait for the next one. 

---Crozier

I guess I don't get it. I thought I love all craft brews... Until today. I always heard the hype of this beer style people called sours. And living by Russian River brewery, figured the first one I would have should be the best. The initial aroma was that of rotten moldy vegetables in the bottom produce drawer in my fridge. Then the taste hit me, Athletes foot mixed with fungus. Before you ask, yes it was fresh from the brewery. No aging was done. Never again will I go out of my way to try a sour. It was the first beer I didn't want to drink. 

---Crozier

Good beer. Your basic recipe for a good IPA Stone style. Perfect beer to have stocked in the fridge so you can have a good beer when doing yard work or some other manly project. 

---Crozier

This one did it for me. Complex flavor, great color with good head, strong dry smell and an amazing bite with a smooth finish. For sure made my top ten list of great beers to enjoy anytime.

beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob:
Good choice of spices. Tastes of fruit zest. Good hops. Lower IBU'S for my taste but very good balance of flavors. Great beer to give your friend that you want to love IPA's. 

---Crozier

Every hop heads dream. First sniff and you think you might be in over your head. Extremely bitter! Love it love it love it! If you like high IBU's then this is a must have on stock for your fridge. 

---Crozier

Good taste. Full body. Good head. Not a bad beer to hang back and relax on.

Good aroma. Never thought I would like the espresso mix but I did. Low bite but the espresso hangs in there from start to finish.
